Wayne County Bar Association v. Naumoff.

[Cite as Wayne Cty. Bar Assn. v. Naumoff (1996), 77 Ohio St.3d 1201.]

(No. 95-2179 Submitted and decided October 1, 1996.)

This cause came on for further consideration upon the filing of an application for reinstatement by respondent Mitchell A. Naumoff, a.k.a. Mitchell Alexander Naumoff, Attorney Registration No. 0037544, last known business address in Barberton, Ohio.

The court coming now to consider its order of February 28, 1996, wherein the court, pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(6)(B)(3), suspended respondent for a period of six months, finds that respondent has substantially complied with that order and with the provisions of Gov.Bar R. V(10)(A). Therefore,

IT IS ORDERED by this court that Mitchell A. Naumoff, a.k.a. Mitchell Alexander Naumoff, be and hereby is, reinstated to the practice of law in the state of Ohio.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the Clerk of this court issue certified copies of this order as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(1), that publication be made as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(2), and that respondent bear the costs of publication.

For earlier case; see Wayne Cty. Bar Assn. v. Naumoff (1996), 74 Ohio St.3d 637, 660 N.E.2d 1177.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Stratton, JJ., concur.
